					<div class="page" style="font-family:Arial;">
                        <div class="text-center">
                            <h3><b>MEMORANDUM OF AGREEMENT</b></h3><br/>
                        </div>
                        <div class="text-justify">
                            <p style="font-size:18px;">
                                This agreement entered into this <span t-esc="context_timestamp(datetime.datetime.now()).strftime('%B %d, %Y')"/> at Koronadal City, Philippines by and between:
                            </p>
                        </div><br/>
                        <div class="text-justify">
                            <p style="font-size:18px;">
                                <b><t class="text-uppercase" t-esc="company_id.name"/>,&#160; </b>&#160;&#160; a company duly organized and registered under the laws of the Republic of the Philippines,
                                with principal office address at Osmeña Street, Koronadal City, herein represented by its &#160;<b><t class="text-uppercase" t-esc="signatory_job_id"/></b>&#160;&#160;,
                                &#160;<b><t class="text-uppercase" t-esc="str(o.get_approvers_name(signatory_id.id)).upper()"/>, </b>&#160;&#160; Filipino, of legal age, <t t-esc="signatory_id.marital"/> and residing at ( Address of the signatory ), herein referred to as the <b>“EMPLOYER”</b>  and
                                &#160;<b><t class="text-uppercase" t-esc="str(o.get_approvers_name(employee_id.id)).upper()"/>,</b>&#160; Filipino, of legal age, with address at <t t-if="not employee_id.barangay_id and employee_id.complete_add">
                                    &#160;<b><t class="text-uppercase" t-esc="employee_id.complete_add"/></b>&#160;
                                </t>
                                <t t-if="employee_id.barangay_id and employee_id.complete_add">
                                    &#160;<b><t class="text-uppercase" t-esc="employee_id.complete_add"/>,  <t t-esc="employee_id.barangay_id.display_name"/></b>&#160;
                                </t>
                                <t t-if="employee_id.barangay_id and not employee_id.complete_add">
                                    &#160;<b><t class="text-uppercase" t-esc="employee_id.barangay_id.display_name"/></b>&#160;
                                </t>
                                <t t-if="not employee_id.barangay_id and not employee_id.complete_add and employee_id.municipality_id">
                                   &#160; <b><t class="text-uppercase" t-esc="employee_id.municipality_id.display_name"/></b>&#160;
                                </t>
                                <t t-if="not employee_id.barangay_id and not employee_id.complete_add and not employee_id.municipality_id and employee_id.province_id">
                                    &#160;<b><t class="text-uppercase" t-esc="employee_id.province_id.display_name"/></b>&#160;
                                </t>
                                <t t-if="not employee_id.barangay_id and not employee_id.complete_add and not employee_id.municipality_id and not employee_id.province_id and employee_id.region_id">
                                    &#160;<b><t class="text-uppercase" t-esc="employee_id.region_id.display_name"/></b>&#160;
                                </t> herein referred to as the <b> “EMPLOYEE.” </b>


                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="text-center">
                            <p style="font-size:18px;"><b>WITNESSETH THAT:</b></p>
                        </div>
                        <table style="font-size:18px;width:100%;border-collapse: collapse;">
                            <tr>
                                <td style="width:2%;padding:4px;text-align:left;vertical-align:center;">
                                </td>
                                <td style="width:3%;padding:4px;text-align:left;vertical-align:center;">
                                    <p style="font-size:18px;"><b>1.</b></p>
                                </td>
                                <td style="width:95%;padding:4px;text-align:justify;vertical-align:center;">
                                    <p style="font-size:18px;"><b>WHEREAS</b>, the <b>EMPLOYER</b> owns and operates the business under the business name of <b><t class="text-uppercase" t-esc="company_id.name"/></b>&#160;;</p>
                                </td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td style="width:2%;padding:4px;text-align:left;vertical-align:center;">
                                </td>
                                <td style="width:3%;padding:4px;text-align:left;vertical-align:center;">
                                    <p style="font-size:18px;"><b>2.</b></p>
                                </td>
                                <td style="width:95%;padding:4px;text-align:justify;vertical-align:center;">
                                    <p style="font-size:18px;"><b>WHEREAS</b>, the <b>EMPLOYER</b>, in its effort to strengthen its organization and
                                        Business Units, desires to employ the services of personnel with technical and
                                        managerial experience and expertise to meet the growing needs of the company;</p>
                                </td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td style="width:2%;padding:4px;text-align:left;vertical-align:center;">
                                </td>
                                <td style="width:3%;padding:4px;text-align:left;vertical-align:center;">
                                    <p style="font-size:18px;"><b>3.</b></p>
                                </td>
                                <td style="width:95%;padding:4px;text-align:justify;vertical-align:center;">
                                    <p style="font-size:18px;"><b>WHEREAS</b>, the <b>EMPLOYER</b> is interested in engaging the services of the <b>EMPLOYEE</b> as CUSTOMER SERVICE REPRESENTATIVE.</p>
                                </td>
                            </tr>
                        </table>
                        <div class="text-left">
                            <p style="font-size:18px;">
                                <b>NOW, THEREFORE,</b> for and in consideration of the foregoing premises, the parties hereby agree as follows:
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <table style="font-size:18px;width:100%;border-collapse: collapse;">
                            <tr>
                                <td style="width:5%;padding:4px;text-align:left;vertical-align:center;">
                                </td>
                                <td style="width:3%;padding:4px;text-align:left;vertical-align:center;">
                                    <p style="font-size:18px;"><b>1.</b></p>
                                </td>
                                <td style="width:92%;padding:4px;text-align:justify;vertical-align:center;">
                                    <p style="font-size:18px;"><b>JOB TITLE AND DESCRIPTION</b></p><br/>
                                    <p>The <b>EMPLOYEE</b> is hired as (Position) &#160;<b><t class="text-uppercase" t-esc="employee_id.job_id.name"/></b>&#160; effective
                                        &#160;<b><t class="text-uppercase" t-esc="time.strftime('%B %d, %Y', time.strptime(employee_id.date_hired,'%Y-%m-%d'))"/></b>&#160; subject to a probationary period of not more than six (6) months.
                                        The probationary period shall be from &#160;<b><t class="text-uppercase" t-esc="time.strftime('%B %d, %Y', time.strptime(employee_id.date_hired,'%Y-%m-%d'))"/></b>&#160; to &#160;<b><t t-esc="o.get_months(employee_id.date_hired, 6)"/></b>&#160;.<br/><br/>
                                        The <b>EMPLOYER</b> shall evaluate the performance of the <b>EMPLOYEE</b> at the end of the 1st,
                                        3rd and 5th months of the probationary employment period based on agreed job requirements
                                        and performance standards. If <b>EMPLOYEE’s</b> performance is to the satisfaction of the EMPLOYER,
                                        the <b>EMPLOYEE</b> will be conferred a REGULAR EMPLOYMENT status by the EMPLOYER.</p>
                                </td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td style="width:5%;padding:4px;text-align:left;vertical-align:center;">
                                </td>
                                <td style="width:3%;padding:4px;text-align:left;vertical-align:center;">
                                    <p style="font-size:18px;"><b>2.</b></p>
                                </td>
                                <td style="width:92%;padding:4px;text-align:justify;vertical-align:center;">
                                    <p style="font-size:18px;"><b>COMPENSATION</b></p><br/>
                                    <p>The <b>EMPLOYEE</b> shall be paid a basic salary of &#160;<b><t t-esc="o.get_num2words(salary)"/> ( P <t t-esc="'{0:,.2f}'.format(salary)"/> )</b> &#160; per month
                                        payable every 10th and 25th days of the month. The <b>EMPLOYEE’s</b> salary will be paid either in cash,
                                        through ATM, by a bank check or by a bank or postal transfer, from which shall be deducted ,
                                        where applicable, the <b>EMPLOYEE’s</b> Social Security System, Philhealth and Pag-ibig contributions,
                                        withholding tax and other government deductions. The paid salary includes compensation for
                                        unworked holidays and mandatory allowance under existing Philippine laws.</p>
                                </td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td style="width:5%;padding:4px;text-align:left;vertical-align:center;">
                                </td>
                                <td style="width:3%;padding:4px;text-align:left;vertical-align:center;">
                                    <p style="font-size:18px;"><b>3.</b></p>
                                </td>
                                <td style="width:92%;padding:4px;text-align:justify;vertical-align:center;">
                                    <p style="font-size:18px;"><b>PERFORMANCE APPRAISAL</b></p><br/>
                                    <p>Upon regularization, the <b>EMPLOYEE</b> accepts the policy of the <b>EMPLOYER</b> to review on a semi-annual
                                        basis the performance of its employees based on agreed AIP/MAP and KRA percentage.
                                        Such criteria shall be prepared by the <b>EMPLOYEE</b> and approved by the immediate superior
                                        of the <b>EMPLOYEE</b> at the beginning of the evaluation period. The <b>EMPLOYEE</b> further recognizes
                                        that failure to achieve minimum satisfactory performance shall be a ground for termination.</p>
                                </td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td style="width:5%;padding:4px;text-align:left;vertical-align:center;">
                                </td>
                                <td style="width:3%;padding:4px;text-align:left;vertical-align:center;">
                                    <p style="font-size:18px;"><b>4.</b></p>
                                </td>
                                <td style="width:92%;padding:4px;text-align:justify;vertical-align:center;">
                                    <p style="font-size:18px;"><b>COMPANY RULES AND REGULATIONS</b></p><br/>
                                    <p>All existing as well as future rules and regulations issued by the <b>EMPLOYER</b> are hereby
                                        deemed incorporated in this contract. The <b>EMPLOYEE</b> recognizes that by signing
                                        this contract, he shall be bound by all such rules and regulations which <b>EMPLOYER</b>
                                        may issue from time to time. On signing this contract, the <b>EMPLOYEE</b> acknowledges his
                                        duty and responsibility to be aware of the rules and regulations of the <b>EMPLOYER</b> regarding
                                        his employment and to fully comply with them in good faith.</p>
                                </td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td style="width:5%;padding:4px;text-align:left;vertical-align:center;">
                                </td>
                                <td style="width:3%;padding:4px;text-align:left;vertical-align:center;">
                                    <p style="font-size:18px;"><b>5.</b></p>
                                </td>
                                <td style="width:92%;padding:4px;text-align:justify;vertical-align:center;">
                                    <p style="font-size:18px;"><b>DISCIPLINARY MEASURES</b></p><br/>
                                    <p>By signing this contract, the <b>EMPLOYEE</b> hereby recognizes the right of the <b>EMPLOYER</b>
                                        to impose disciplinary measures or sanctions which may include but are not limited to,
                                        termination of employment, suspensions, fines, salary deductions, withdrawal of benefits,
                                        loss of privileges, for any and all infractions, acts or omission, irrespective that such
                                        infractions, act or omission constitute a ground for termination.</p>
                                </td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td style="width:5%;padding:4px;text-align:left;vertical-align:center;">
                                </td>
                                <td style="width:3%;padding:4px;text-align:left;vertical-align:center;">
                                    <p style="font-size:18px;"><b>6.</b></p>
                                </td>
                                <td style="width:92%;padding:4px;text-align:justify;vertical-align:center;">
                                    <p style="font-size:18px;"><b>BUSINESS CODE OF CONDUCT</b></p><br/>
                                    <p>The position of &#160;<b><t class="text-uppercase" t-esc="employee_id.job_id.name"/> </b>&#160; is one of trust and confidence.
                                        The <b>EMPLOYEE</b> shall act in a manner characterized by transparency, accountability
                                        and fairness.<br/><br/>
                                        On signing this contract, the <b>EMPLOYEE</b> agrees that during the course of employment and immediately
                                        following the termination of the relationship with the <b>EMPLOYER</b> for any reason, whether with or
                                        without good cause or for any or no cause, at the option either of the <b>EMPLOYER</b> or the <b>EMPLOYEE</b>, 
                                        with or without notice, the <b>EMPLOYEE</b> will NOT, without the prior written consent of the <b>EMPLOYER</b>, a)
                                        serve as a partner, employee, consultant, officer, director, manager, agent, associate, investor,
                                        or otherwise, or b) directly or indirectly, own, purchase, organize or take preparatory steps for
                                        the organization of, or c) build, design, finance, acquire, lease, operate, manage, invest in, work
                                        or consult for or otherwise affiliate with, any business in competition with or otherwise similar
                                        to the <b>EMPLOYER’s</b> business within the <b>EMPLOYER’s</b> area of operation for a period of five (5) years ,
                                        nor shall the <b>EMPLOYEE’s</b> relatives up to the third civil degree of consanguinity be involved in any
                                        business that directly competes with the <b>EMPLOYER’s</b> business.
                                    </p>
                                </td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td style="width:5%;padding:4px;text-align:left;vertical-align:center;">
                                </td>
                                <td style="width:3%;padding:4px;text-align:left;vertical-align:center;">
                                    <p style="font-size:18px;"><b>7.</b></p>
                                </td>
                                <td style="width:92%;padding:4px;text-align:justify;vertical-align:center;">
                                    <p style="font-size:18px;"><b>TERMINATION OF EMPLOYMENT</b></p><br/>
                                    <p>Aside from the just and authorized causes for the termination of employment
                                        enumerated in Art. 282 to 284 of the Labor Code, the following acts and/or omissions
                                        shall, without limitation, similarly constitute just and authorized grounds for the
                                        termination of employment by the <b>EMPLOYER</b> and/or grounds for the <b>EMPLOYER</b> to impose disciplinary measures:
                                    </p><br/>
                                    <table style="font-size:18px;width:100%;border-collapse: collapse;">
                                        <tr>
                                            <td style="width:5%;padding:4px;text-align:left;vertical-align:center;">
                                            </td>
                                            <td style="width:3%;padding:4px;text-align:left;vertical-align:center;">
                                                <p style="font-size:18px;"><b>a).</b></p>
                                            </td>
                                            <td style="width:92%;padding:4px;text-align:justify;vertical-align:center;">
                                                <p>Intentional or unintentional violation of the <b>EMPLOYER’s</b> policies, rules
                                                    and regulations as embodied in the Code of Discipline;</p>
                                            </td>
                                        </tr>
                                        <tr>
                                            <td style="width:5%;padding:4px;text-align:left;vertical-align:center;">
                                            </td>
                                            <td style="width:3%;padding:4px;text-align:left;vertical-align:center;">
                                                <p style="font-size:18px;"><b>b).</b></p>
                                            </td>
                                            <td style="width:92%;padding:4px;text-align:justify;vertical-align:center;">
                                                <p>Commissions of an act that leads to loss of confidence on the part of the <b>EMPLOYER</b>
                                                    with regard to the <b>EMPLOYEE’s</b> ability to satisfactorily perform the duties and
                                                    requirements of <b>EMPLOYEE’s</b> employment;</p>
                                            </td>
                                        </tr>
                                        <tr>
                                            <td style="width:5%;padding:4px;text-align:left;vertical-align:center;">
                                            </td>
                                            <td style="width:3%;padding:4px;text-align:left;vertical-align:center;">
                                                <p style="font-size:18px;"><b>c).</b></p>
                                            </td>
                                            <td style="width:92%;padding:4px;text-align:justify;vertical-align:center;">
                                                <p>Failure of the <b>EMPLOYEE</b> to meet the agreed AIP/MAP for the 6-month probationary period;</p>
                                            </td>
                                        </tr>
                                        <tr>
                                            <td style="width:5%;padding:4px;text-align:left;vertical-align:center;">
                                            </td>
                                            <td style="width:3%;padding:4px;text-align:left;vertical-align:center;">
                                                <p style="font-size:18px;"><b>d).</b></p>
                                            </td>
                                            <td style="width:92%;padding:4px;text-align:justify;vertical-align:center;">
                                                <p>Other similar acts, omissions, and/or events.</p>
                                            </td>
                                        </tr>
                                    </table><br/>
                                </td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td style="width:5%;padding:4px;text-align:left;vertical-align:center;">
                                </td>
                                <td style="width:3%;padding:4px;text-align:left;vertical-align:center;">
                                </td>
                                <td style="width:92%;padding:4px;text-align:justify;vertical-align:center;">
                                    <p>This contract of employment may be terminated by the <b>EMPLOYER</b> for any of the foregoing
                                        grounds upon due notice and opportunity to be heard as required by law.
                                        In the event the <b>EMPLOYEE</b> wishes to pre-terminate this contract of employment
                                        for any reason, <b>EMPLOYEE</b> must submit a written notice to the <b>EMPLOYER</b> thirty (30)
                                        days prior to the effective date of termination.

                                    </p>
                                </td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td style="width:5%;padding:4px;text-align:left;vertical-align:center;">
                                </td>
                                <td style="width:3%;padding:4px;text-align:left;vertical-align:center;">
                                </td>
                                <td style="width:92%;padding:4px;text-align:justify;vertical-align:center;">
                                    <p>Upon termination of this employment, the <b>EMPLOYEE</b> shall promptly account for, return,
                                        and deliver to the <b>EMPLOYER</b> at the <b>EMPLOYER’s</b> head office, <b>EMPLOYEE’s</b> ID Cards, Code
                                        of Discipline Manual. Employee Handbook and all properties of <b>EMPLOYER</b> which may have
                                        been assigned or entrusted to <b>EMPLOYEE’s</b> care or custody.
                                    </p>
                                </td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td style="width:5%;padding:4px;text-align:left;vertical-align:center;">
                                </td>
                                <td style="width:3%;padding:4px;text-align:left;vertical-align:center;">
                                    <p style="font-size:18px;"><b>8.</b></p>
                                </td>
                                <td style="width:92%;padding:4px;text-align:justify;vertical-align:center;">
                                    <p style="font-size:18px;"><b>CONFIDENTIALITY</b></p><br/>
                                    <p>The <b>EMPLOYER</b> agrees that upon commencement of the <b>EMPLOYEE’s</b> employment, it will
                                        make available all necessary information that will enable the <b>EMPLOYEE</b> to
                                        optimize performance. The <b>EMPLOYEE</b> agrees to use such confidential information solely
                                        for the <b>EMPLOYER’s</b> benefit. The <b>EMPLOYEE</b> understands and agrees that CONFIDENTIAL INFORMATION
                                        means any proprietary information, technical data, trade secrets or know-how, including,
                                        but not limited to, markets, software, developments, inventions, processes, formulas,
                                        technology, designs, drawings, engineering, hardware, configuration information, marketing,
                                        finances, or other business information disclosed by the <b>EMPLOYER</b> to the <b>EMPLOYEE</b> either
                                        directly or indirectly in writing, orally or by drawings or observation of parts or equipment;</p>
                                </td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td style="width:5%;padding:4px;text-align:left;vertical-align:center;">
                                </td>
                                <td style="width:3%;padding:4px;text-align:left;vertical-align:center;">
                                    <p style="font-size:18px;"><b>9.</b></p>
                                </td>
                                <td style="width:92%;padding:4px;text-align:justify;vertical-align:center;">
                                    <p style="font-size:18px;"><b>SEPARABILITY CAUSE</b></p><br/>
                                    <p>If any provision of this document shall be construed to be illegal or invalid,
                                        they shall not affect the legality, validity and enforceability of the other provisions
                                        of this document; the illegal or invalid provision shall be deleted from this document
                                        and deemed no longer incorporated herein but all other provisions of this document shall
                                        continue to have effect.<br/><br/>
                                    </p>
                                </td>
                            </tr>
                        </table>
                        <div class="text-justify">
                            <p style="font-size:18px;"><b>IN WITNESS WHEREOF</b>&#160;,  the parties have executed this document as of the date and place first mentioned.
                                <br/></p>
